WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified standard reference for the DVB BlueBook incorporating
T/UWA 005 (HDR Vivid) into the DVB core video coding specification for
broadcast and broadband services, published March 2026.

WHY IT EXISTS
The DVB BlueBook marks the formal adoption of HDR Vivid by European
broadcast infrastructure. GIOP cross-references this with the HDR
Vivid standard to provide a complete DVB-compliant delivery path.

HOW IT WORKS
The BlueBook defines:
  1. How HDR Vivid metadata is carried in DVB transport streams (MPEG-TS
     and DASH).
  2. The signalling descriptors for service information (SI) that
     identify HDR Vivid content.
  3. The expected ETSI standard publication timeline (target May 2026).

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- European DVB broadcast networks
- GIOP HDR delivery to DVB-compliant receivers.

WHO USES IT
Broadcast engineers; DVB receiver manufacturers.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Provides the DVB-specific transport and signalling specification for
HDR Vivid, enabling GIOP to generate fully compliant broadcast streams.

